  "informal_statement": "Reflecting a point (x, y) over the y-axis to (-x, y) preserves its squared distance to any point (0, qy) lying on the y-axis, since the point's x-coordinate is squared either way (x^2 = (-x)^2).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Expand both squared-distance expressions; they are identical polynomials since x^2 = (-x)^2. Closes by ring.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem reflection_over_y_axis (x y qy : ℝ) : x ^ 2 + (y - qy) ^ 2 = (-x) ^ 2 + (y - qy) ^ 2",
